    <title>DEG2RAD Convert From Degrees To Radians</title>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Section: <ref refid="sec_mathfunctions_1sec_mathfunctions" kindref="member">Mathematical Functions</ref> </para><sect1 id="vtkwidgets_vtkxyplotwidget_1Usage">
<title>Usage</title>
<para>Converts the argument from degrees to radians. The syntax for its use is <verbatim>   y = deg2rad(x)
</verbatim> where <computeroutput>x</computeroutput> is a numeric array. Conversion is done by simply multiplying <computeroutput>x</computeroutput> by <computeroutput>pi/180</computeroutput>. </para></sect1>
